.cs 3 on
.item 'SET LINE Command' 'Added on 12/09/82 by EAB'
.boxon
SET LINE {name|'name'}
.*       <----------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SET LINE name
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SET LINE command allows you to change the user name set by SET NAME and
displayed in the SHOW LINE/SHOW LINES responses.  SET LINE overrides the SET
NAME command for the current terminal session.

.* SELECT 'SET LINE Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION NAME
.optix name
name|'name'\\\\\specifies a user name that can be up to 20 characters long.
                The name must be enclosed in apostrophes or quotation marks if
                a blank is specified as one of the characters of the name.  If
                name is null (i.e.\'' or ""), the user name will be reset to
                that of the SET NAME.
.cs 3 off
